        (
            id: "restaurant",
            name: "Restaurant at the End of the Universe",
            desc: "Acturan A-POP wafts through invisible speakers, accompanied by the occasional sound of imploding galaxies. A tasteful sign declares this to be the Restaurant at the End of the Universe, though it appears to be between dinner rushes. Tables float slightly above the ground and rearrange themselves when you\'re not looking. A host\'s podium stands to one side with an open reservation book, but the host is nowhere to be seen. Restrooms lie to the south bearing a sign in fancy script reading:\n\nPatio seating stretches farther east.",
