        (
            id: "loading-dock",
            name: "Useless Loading Dock",
            desc: "The so-called loading dock juts ten feet *above* the ground, with no ramp, stairs, or apparent means of access and a [[i]]baffling[[/i]] loading door thirty [[b]]meters[[/b]] wide but a mere four [[b]]centimeters[[/b]] tall. A conveyor belt runs from the building wall to the edge of the dock, then loops straight back in again without touching anything.\n\nA bronze plaque is inset into the wall at the far edge of the dock.\n\nIt\'s unclear what this facility ever needed to load or unload — or who would deliver to the side of a remote building halfway up a mountain.\n\nA paved walkway wraps around the building in both directions.",
