            id: "observation-room",
            name: "Field Observation Room",
            desc: "Thick observation windows, long since spiderwebbed with cracks, overlook what should be Room AA-3B—but only darkness and occasional flashes of unreality appear beyond. Opposite those, another set of windows provide a view to a cavernous chamber with a large, obsidian obelisk standing ominously near its center. Abandoned swivel chairs and battered clipboards litter the room. A faint smell of burnt ozone hangs in the air.\n\nA console flickers near one of the broad windows.",
